events.name: San Antonio Spurs at Miami Heat

headlines.description: — Rookie Kel’el Ware scored 25 points to match his season high, Duncan Robinson added 21 on 5-of-7 3-shooting and the Miami Heat beat the San Antonio Spurs 128-107 on Sunday.
headlines.shortLinkText: Rookie Kel’el Ware matches season high with 25 points in the Heat's 128-107 win over the Spurs

headlines.description: — Nikola Jokic had 20 points, 14 rebounds, 10 assists and three blocks without playing the fourth quarter and the Denver Nuggets rolled to a 113-100 win over the Orlando Magic on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Nikola Jokic's triple-double leads Nuggets past Magic 113-100

headlines.description: — Giannis Antetokounmpo had 34 points and 15 rebounds to help the Milwaukee Bucks beat the short-handed Philadelphia 76ers 123-109 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Antetokounmpo scores 34 points in Bucks' 123-109 victory over the short-handed 76ers

events.name: Brooklyn Nets at Oklahoma City Thunder

headlines.description: — Shai Gilgeous-Alexander had 27 points and 10 assists in three quarters, and the Oklahoma City Thunder beat the Brooklyn Nets 127-101 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Gilgeous-Alexander has 27 points, 10 assists to lead Thunder past Nets 127-101

events.name: Los Angeles Lakers at LA Clippers

headlines.description: — Norman Powell scored 22 points, James Harden added 21 points and 12 assists and the Los Angeles Clippers defeated LeBron James and the Los Angeles Lakers 116-102 on Sunday night in the Lakers' first visit to the new Intuit Dome.
headlines.shortLinkText: Powell and the Clippers beat James and the Lakers 116-102 in Lakers' first visit to Intuit Dome

events.name: Chicago Bulls at Portland Trail Blazers

headlines.description: — Scoot Henderson had 25 points and the Portland Trail Blazers snapped five-game losing streak with a 113-102 victory over the Chicago Bulls on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Scoot Henderson scores 25 points, Trail Blazers beat Bulls 113-102 to end 5-game skid

headlines.description: — Domantas Sabonis had 29 points and 18 rebounds, and the Sacramento Kings beat the Washington Wizards 123-100 on Sunday night.
headlines.shortLinkText: Domantas Sabonis has 29 points, 18 rebounds as Kings beat Wizards 123-100
